The paper proposes waveform design strategies for multi-antenna multi-sine WPT over frequency-selective channels, which involves signal processing, communication, and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data communication and signal processing. The paper also involves system-level optimization and control, which suggests the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another likely category. Moreover, the paper proposes novel algorithms for optimizing codebooks, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, suggesting the possibility of cs.MM (Machine Learning) as another likely category. The paper also involves networked systems and wireless communication, which suggests the possibility of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as another likely category. Finally, the paper involves energy harvesting and wireless power transfer, which suggests the possibility of cs.CE (Computers and Society) as another likely category, which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing technologies.
